# GoodData Migration Toolkit - Testing Guidelines

## Requirements

All new code must have unit tests. Test:
- Happy path (normal expected usage)
- Error cases (API failures, missing data, invalid input)
- Edge cases (empty inputs, None values, boundary conditions)

## Stack

- **pytest** — primary framework
- **pytest-mock** — mocking via `mocker` fixture

## Fixture Placement

- `tests/conftest.py` — broadly applicable fixtures only (used across many test files)
- `tests/fixtures/` — domain-specific fixtures (e.g., `scheduled_exports_fixtures.py`)

Do not put domain-specific fixtures in `conftest.py`.

## Test Data

- Use real sanitized data from `tests/data/` (JSON/CSV files with real Legacy/Cloud structures)
- Do not create synthetic data when real examples exist
- Mock all external calls (API, file I/O) — tests must not hit real APIs
